1
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:34,940
With so much information,

2
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,880
I don't know how much of it is true

3
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:38,080
and how much is false.

4
00:00:48,520 --> 00:00:50,480
Do you think the address she left is real?

5
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:52,640
We can figure out from her ID number

6
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:53,600
that she is seventeen.

7
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:55,720
But she filled in twenty-seven for her age.

8
00:00:55,720 --> 00:00:58,000
It shows she never intended to give her real information

9
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:58,840
to the doctor.

10
00:00:58,840 --> 00:01:00,360
Then most of the content here

11
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:01,440
is not credible.

12
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:03,160
But sometimes when people lie,

13
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:04,720
it's just a subconscious act.

14
00:01:04,720 --> 00:01:06,640
A lie is not necessarily a complete lie;

15
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:09,280
it's just a packaged and modified truth.

16
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:11,640
Dongcheng Jiayuan really exists.

17
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,240
I see what you mean.

18
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:15,840
The Dongcheng Jiayuan she wrote down must be fake.

19
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:18,039
The reason she wrote Dongcheng Jiayuan

20
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:20,940
shows she often passes by or is familiar with it.

21
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,800
Jiela Internet Cafe,

22
00:01:23,320 --> 00:01:24,600
Feiyue Gym,

23
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:26,600
they are all places she has been to.

24
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:28,840
She also wrote Dongcheng Jiayuan,

25
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:29,960
which means this area

26
00:01:29,960 --> 00:01:32,039
should be within her frequent activity range.

27
00:01:32,039 --> 00:01:34,560
If we exclude Dongcheng Jiayuan,

28
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:36,280
there are three left.

29
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:36,880
Two.

30
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:38,720
This Lihua Yihaoyuan

31
00:01:38,720 --> 00:01:40,400
is a newly built high-end neighborhood.

32
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,400
They are all large flat apartments,

33
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,800
with an average price of over 40,000.

34
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:45,330
Do you remember what that person was wearing?

35
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,520
I remember she seemed to be wearing Arc'teryx.

36
00:01:54,759 --> 00:01:56,020
It's quite expensive.

37
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,440
I don't think so.

38
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,360
The spelling of Arc'teryx is like this.

39
00:02:03,360 --> 00:02:05,640
The apostrophe is in the top right corner of ARC.

40
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,920
If I remember correctly,

41
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:09,000
the one on hers was in the bottom right corner of ARC,

42
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:10,479
which means she was wearing a knockoff.

43
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:12,640
If she was really wearing a knockoff,

44
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,960
then her financial situation shouldn't be that good.

45
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,160
She couldn't afford that kind of house.

46
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:19,680
Sir,

47
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,540
Liyuan Neighborhood.

48
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:27,600
One out of two.

49
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,610
That's a fifty percent chance.

50
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,000
No need to go to the next neighborhood.

51
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,600
This is it.

52
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:06,920
Okay.

53
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:07,920
Everyone's here.

54
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:08,280
So,

55
00:03:08,640 --> 00:03:10,640
each of you will take charge of one trash can

56
00:03:10,640 --> 00:03:11,720
and help me find something.

57
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,600
No way, we can't do this.

58
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:15,040
Listen to me.

59
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,480
My mom accidentally

60
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:18,360
threw away something very important to me,

61
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:20,440
but she forgot which trash can she threw it in.

62
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,960
The surveillance cameras in our neighborhood are broken,

63
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,760
but this item is really important to me.

64
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,320
I'm begging you all.

65
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:25,380
I'll pay you extra.

66
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,200
I see.

67
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:26,860
No problem.

68
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,480
Okay.

69
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:28,960
As for what I lost,

70
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,760
it's not convenient for me to say.

71
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:32,520
But the garbage bag I lost has bloody gauze in it.

72
00:03:32,520 --> 00:03:34,600
So if anyone finds bloody gauze, call me,

73
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:35,079
okay?

74
00:03:35,079 --> 00:03:35,560
Okay.

75
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,320
Come on, get moving, hurry.

76
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,320
Found it!

77
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:15,280
Wait a minute.

78
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,519
It's full of glass.

79
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,200
There's quite a lot of blood on this,

80
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,200
and iodophor was clearly used.

81
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:27,860
She probably didn't use this.

82
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:32,890
Go keep looking.

83
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,700
Keep looking, everyone look.

84
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:37,580
I'll give an extra thousand to whoever finds it.

85
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:50,480
Here, found it!

86
00:04:58,440 --> 00:04:59,240
Where did you find it?

87
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,560
In this takeout bag.

88
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:05,760
Liyuan Neighborhood, Building 6, Unit 2, 204.

89
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,480
Open the door!

90
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,800
Open the door! Open the door!

91
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,040
What happened to your face?

92
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:12,810
My plastic surgery failed.

93
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:17,320
Are you the one who told Huangmao to take the video?

94
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:20,760
Is it you?

95
00:06:31,840 --> 00:06:32,640
Found it.

96
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,080
Not bad.

97
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,560
Once you get the video and confirm there are no backups,

98
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,720
you can leave.

99
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:40,440
Don't meddle in other affairs.

100
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,840
Wait for my next mission.

101
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:10,680
Didn't you two have a pretty good relationship?

102
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,140
Why did it end up like this?

103
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:23,160
Because her grades are better than mine.

104
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,080
She's prettier than me.

105
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:24,960
She's better than me at everything.

106
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:25,720
Why?

107
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:26,840
I mean, you...

108
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:31,560
Never mind.

109
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,200
Anyway, you've received the punishment you deserve.

110
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,460
Take care of yourself.

111
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:44,840
Eat up quickly.

112
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:46,320
If you go hungry,

113
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:47,980
your dad will be heartbroken.

114
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:05,160
After I finish everything

115
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,560
and my daughter returns,

116
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:08,760
you must hide well.

117
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:11,040
Empty threats are meaningless,

118
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:13,040
but they let you vent your emotions.

119
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,650
Do you need to say a few more?

120
00:08:14,880 --> 00:08:15,640
No need.

121
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:18,290
I just want to give you some instructions.

122
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,960
My daughter doesn't eat cilantro,

123
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:20,880
or chili.

124
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,860
Her favorite is tomato and egg stir-fry,

125
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:25,780
but remember to add some vinegar.

126
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,300
That's all for now.

127
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:28,760
Tell me.

128
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:31,080
What do you want me to do next?

129
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,610
You cooperated well today.

130
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:35,000
If you keep this up,

131
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,200
your daughter will definitely be comfortable.

132
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:39,320
But this is just the beginning.

133
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:40,880
Let's call it a day.

134
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,600
Get a good night's rest

135
00:08:42,880 --> 00:08:44,540
and wait for my call tomorrow.

136
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:51,160
The person in the video is your daughter.

137
00:08:52,360 --> 00:08:55,680
What exactly is the countdown on your bracelet?

138
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:57,080
Also, do you really not know

139
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,800
what is inside your body?

140
00:09:02,280 --> 00:09:03,720
What exactly happened?

141
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:05,680
Nothing happened.

142
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,980
Your condition doesn't allow you to run around.

143
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:11,810
I know you might have things you can't say.

144
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,200
But if you need help,

145
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,770
let me know anytime.

146
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:19,000
Okay, got it.

147
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:19,800
Thank you.

148
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:22,860
It's getting late.

149
00:09:23,520 --> 00:09:25,120
You should go home early too.

150
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:33,880
What's wrong?

151
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,820
Do you want me to walk you home?

152
00:09:36,640 --> 00:09:37,280
No.

153
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:40,400
I think you might need some help right now.

154
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:42,800
How can you help me?

155
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:44,360
I...

156
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:45,760
How about this?

157
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,240
Can you buy me a bottle of water?

158
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:48,440
I'm a little thirsty.

159
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,520
What does this mean?

160
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,850
This is my phone number.

161
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:04,120
I think

162
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,120
you want me to buy water for you

163
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,560
and then take the opportunity to leave.

164
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,160
Don't worry, I won't.

165
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:03,100
Help me look into someone.

166
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:20,900
Did you sleep okay last night?

167
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,000
Thanks to you,

168
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:22,940
it was fine.

169
00:11:23,240 --> 00:11:24,840
Then you should cherish it.

170
00:11:24,840 --> 00:11:27,000
You'll have less and less time to rest from now on.

171
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,200
A new mission is here.

172
00:11:50,680 --> 00:11:51,610
Production Team

173
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:54,600
Action Team
